  "response": "Maggi noodles have various formulations depending on the region in which they are sold. Generally speaking, the tastemaker included in Maggi noodles is vegetarian in most countries, including India. However, ingredients and formulations can vary, and there might be specific regional variations that contain non-vegetarian substances.\n\nIf you have concerns about whether the Maggi tastemaker you have purchased contains non-vegetarian ingredients, it's best to check the packaging where the ingredients are listed or contact the manufacturer directly for detailed and specific information.",
